The generals believe that this new automatic rifle will influence the conflict there with the Taliban and "go change the game" for their benefit.
The new weapon is like a super-precision cannon
Its projectiles are laser guided with a precision of a few meters.
Special ammunition of 25 mm calibre developed for this rifle and containing a highly breaking explosive, actually works as small grenades.
Ammunition can be programmed in such a way that it will explode in contact with the target but also at any point in their ballistic trajectory.
It can therefore be used against an enemy who hides behind an obstacle, a wall or a ditch.
Nor is it protected from above and when it falls on it a deadly rain of steel shrapnel, it can put it out of combat as well.
According to Richard Audette, who took part in the development of the XM-25, the new rifle is the first infantry weapon that uses "intelligent" technology.
"The soldier essentially uses it in such a way that he finds the target, sends him a laser beam that determines the distance, thus obtains a precise point of sight, according to which he corrects his target site and presses on the relaxation.
"Let's say you've targeted 543 meters."
"When you press the trigger, the weapon loads and pulls at a distance of 543 meters more or less 1, 2, 3 meters," said Audette.
400 jobs outsourced
Fujitsu Group relocates its subsidiary from Bad Homburg to Frankfurt.
