Their focus on Twitter coverage is controversial.
In the interviews, some journalists stated that the assertion that instant news was more incendiary than press releases submitted more slowly was a luddist view that would impoverish the Court's policy of media coverage of future trials.
However, some lawyers stated that courts of appeal were often attracted to arguments that social and technological change required adaptation by the courts.
