"This is an ineffective system in which criminal groups fill a gap in certain areas where the city does not provide certain services."
The report indicates that the FSB is mixing the money of the largest companies and that the police are targeting the small ones.
One source, he said, "explained that business owners in Moscow understood that it was better to obtain protection from MVD and FSB (rather than organized crime groups) because they not only have more weapons, more means and more power than criminal groups but they are also protected by law."
